  "description": "11e 12.07-12.08 GLOBAL Consolidate step, played end-to-end as a human. The whole fight phase runs through the real UI: three activations (Warboss P2, then Custodian Guard and Telemon Dreadnought P1 — the Telemon is engaged only at the 11e 2-inch ER) via FightSelectionDialog unit buttons, Ka'tah stance buttons, PileInDialog skip, AttackAssignmentDialog all-to-target + confirm. Then End Fight Phase enters the new global Consolidate step: the ACTIVE player (P2) gets the ConsolidationStepDialog first and passes with End Consolidation (consolidation is optional per unit at 11e), then P1 picks the Custodian Guard, DRAGS a model with real mouse-motion events (drag_board), confirms, and ends their half with the Telemon deliberately unmoved. The phase then completes. Setup-only privileges: CP zeroed to suppress stratagem prompts not under test; model wounds inflated so no unit dies (deterministic aliveness for the drag target). Every in-game decision is a real click or drag.",
